Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high
heat. Add @ground beef{10%ounce} and season with @dried thyme{1%teaspoon},
@garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up
meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Swap in beef for pork.

While pork cooks, wash and dry produce.

Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1%unit}. Remove and discard any large
stems from @kale{4%ounce}.

To #pot{} with pork, add beans, @chicken stock concentrate{3%unit}, and @water{3%cups}.
Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer.

> For 4 servings, use 6 cups water.

Stir in kale and @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
kale is wilted and couscous is tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @crème fraîche{2%tablespoon}. Taste and season with
salt and pepper if desired.

Divide soup between bowls. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon} and
serve.

> TIP: If you have a lemon on hand, squeeze some over top for added flavor!

> Ground Beef is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.